caption: Very delicious salads and great employees would come here again 10/10
The customer was awesome! The young lady was very helpful bc it was my first time trying it out!! The salad was good! Of course I had takeout! #yum

I have been religiously going to this location for past 1.5 months. They have great selection of salads and bowls. Quality is excellent. Service is fast and good. Kristina has been super friendly and is always suggesting new dishes to try.
Best healthy bowls! Quality is amazing. Big portions. Service is super quick. Employees are super friendly! Shout out to Kristina.😊
Happy to see one of my favorite spots made it through the chaos of the last 6 months. Delicious and healthy.
Great place for tasty health food. Good place to catch up with friends. Had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again. This place has good reviews for a reason.
Good food but too much salt!! It's unbearable .I will not eat from this chain again.

My favorite spot for quality health food. Service is excellent even when they are busy. Next time I'll be back with my coworkers. The bill was appropriate. They have so many good reviews for a reason.
Great place for health food. Nice place to meet and catch up with family. Had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. The bill was good for how much you get.
Good healthy options

Sweetgreen is the best salad place!!! Super fast and nice interior. A bit pricey but I guess it’s worth it. Best pick is Harvest bowl with blackened chicken, medium sauce. Their goat cheese adds very distinct sour flavor to the salad which i like.

Consistently inconsistent. After a recent visit, I had a few issues with my order. I can't say I'm surprised as I've had problems with my orders (salad being sandy, skimpy bowls, etc.) that have kept me away in the past. However, I think today will be my last visit.  My order was scheduled for a 1:00 pick up. I got there at 1:00 and there was a huge crowd around an empty pick up shelf. Note that I pre-ordered on the app. People were slowly receiving their orders but I still had to wait till 1:20 to get mine. When I did get my salad, there was a giant kale stock right on top--not edible.  I understand things happen, but I feel like all Chicago locations have huge inconsistencies. And when you're paying $10-$15 a salad you better be getting something worth singing about every single time!
Too pricey. $15 for a salad that doesn't even taste good
Salads are healthy and taste good.  Employees very unfriendly. Doesn't seem like they enjoy working there.
Tasty and A+ customer service

Good place for Salads . Good for vegetarians and Vegans . However could be expensive for some . Consider 10$ for atleast one salad . Recommended to order online if visiting during busy hours . They use compostible cutlery's please do not trash and compost them . Save environment .

Fast, casual salads and bowls is the wave. Long line but it went super quick. Great selection of salads and bowls to choose from. I ordered the Chicken Pesto Parm and it was delicious. The bowls are super hearty and you get a lot of food for the price. I would highly recommend this spot for a quick lunch.  Always say “YES” to a slice of bread.

I usually love sweet green but it feels like this location is always out of something.  Like chicken or nuts.   I like the guacamole greens salad and they always seem to have to modify it.  Whoever the manager is doing the ordering should try to plan the business needs better.  Step it up sweet green! You guys have so much potential!

Worst sweetgreen- employees have an attitude that worsens with every ingredient you add to bowl. If you order on Uber eats they won't deliver even half of your order. This location just doesnt give a damn. Avoid if you can
The BBQ chicken salad is heaven.
(Translated by Google) Simple but tasty. Well attended!  (Original) Sencillo pero gustoso. Bien atendido!
I’ve gone to other locations and haven’t had an issue. But here the falafel was over cooked and the hummus was salty. Very disappointing!
Perfect place for a healthy meal! Fresh veggies and good quality ingredients.

We've eaten at Sweetgreens elsewhere and had a great experience, but this was dismal. Firstly, the wait was ridiculously long for such a short queue. Then, when we finally ordered, the server waited until half way through making our salad to tell us they'd run out of the main ingredient in the salad - falafel! Fair enough if you're run out, just let the customer know up front so they can change their order. They were also really stingy with toppings, so we mainly just got a bowl of lettuce and salty dressing. We were very, very unimpressed.
Great salads.  Awesome service.
Fresh greens and delicious sauce
I like the salads, the wait can be long but slightly overpriced!
Elote bowl was one of the best salads I've ever had!

Love all the customizable healthy options here! There was a line out the door when I went and it did not move quickly to say the least. They did mess up a few ingredients in my order but when corrected they were nice about fixing it. It was such a busy evening that I don’t want to judge them on it so I will have to go back and give them another chance because the salad I got was delicious! (Avocado Lentil)
The service was very kind and attentive. The bill was reasonable.
Epic Salas, get the Harvest bowl
Loved this place ‘til I found a huge beetle in my elote bowl today :(
Friendly helpful staff and good food. Very filling. Had curried chickpea bowl.

It's okay.... overpriced, tasty salads. You can do better than this at home for A LOT cheaper. IMHO Roots in Charlottesville VA does a lot better than this place.  Also, got medium dressing and it was basically swimming in dressing. I would go with "little" dressing if you decide to go here.

I was super excited to try the restaurant and I was shocked by the service and rudeness of the staff. I am sad because I know so much about the story of the restaurant and why it started and I’m sure the 3 founders wouldn’t be happy by what’s going on! She was literally throwing the spoon and went to the cashier without us being done!!!!!
I like this place. If you’re looking for “healthy” this place is the epitome!  Some may think the salads are a bit pricey, but they fill you up and are delicious.
Best salads and bowls! Quality is amazing. Big portions. I literally crave one everyday! I've tried about 6 different salads/bowls and loved them all.
I really enjoyed the salad but It was a bit pricey

I enjoy sweetgreen occasionally. It's pretty darn expensive but also really tasty and friendly for dietary restriction. You can't go wrong with the harvest bowl and today I enjoyed the spicy Thai salad. I would love to see a better balance of greens to toppings, as I think that's what bugs me about the price. If they got the amount of toppings to greens ratio right, no brainer.

Stumbled across this gem while cruising downtown. The first thing that you notice are the helpful and friendly staff as soon as you walk in. Walked in for a snack and got an entire meal. If you’re picky and want a flavorful, tasty salad stop by!!
Not the happiest employees and don’t accept cash! Can’t support a business that won’t accept legal tender...LAME!
The service here is above par. Prices were good for how much you get.

I'm tired spending my hard earned money here. I don't care about the grumpy attitude of the people serving up my $15 salad, but half the time the bowl is barely half full - I'm ready to just start telling them I don't want it once I see they are making it skimpy. For the insane prices this place charges, the salad should be full and consistent.
Service is always friendly and all the ingredients are super fresh! The dressings are amazing too!

A great place for a healthy meal. The salads are huge! They seem to be totally customizable as well, right down to how much dressing you want. I was served very quickly, and you should note that they don't take cash. Would definitely go back!
Lines are long during weekdays lunch for a good reason.... sweetgreen is fantastic. Kind staff. Yum!
Loved it!  I would highly recommend.  It was my favorite meal during my last visit.
Horrible! Dirty counters, no A/C. I asked for no cheese but my request was in vain. Every ingredient is contaminated by another due to sloppy service.
Excellent food, great service and very healthy options. Totally recommended.
Tasty
Customer service is hit or miss, they are abrupt and unfriendly
Good bowls

This place makes a great salad! I recommend for lunch or dinner. It gets pretty crowded at lunch time so you may want to order ahead by using their app. The service is a bit hit or miss. Sometimes the staff is friendly, sometimes not. I still go here, but don’t always leave with a smile.

This was my first time at Sweetgreen, and it was great! A colleague and his baby daughter were in town, and we needed to find a stroller- and kid friendly place that would also accommodate a  vegan and nut allergies. The staff is extremely helpful and knowledgeable. And they’re friendly and accommodating. I had the vegan shroom bowl which was very tasty. Lots a fresh greens, tofu, and marinated mushrooms. I was thinking that there might be too much food and was ready to take home leftovers, but I ate the whole thing. It was that good. I also appreciate the environmental friendliness of the place. Definitely a go-to for a downtown Chicago lunch at Michigan and Randolph.
I loved it wish we had one in Kansas.
Soooo delicious! It's just very expensive and the yuppie crowd is annoying af.
The staff is very friendly and the salad is fresh as ever. I'd highly recommend going with the curry chicken salad bowl. Definitely worth the money!!

The salad just wasn't good and staff wasn't very attentive. I'm fine with hipster-esque places but I was disappointed they didn't have a traditional soda fountain. The salad was in a big bowl but there really want much there. Expensive for what you get. Their dressing selection for salads was almost all vinaigrettes and the one I had was not great. I think what caused the salad to taste bad was the lime juice. I love lime juice but the combination of that and an acidic vinaigrette made the salad almost sour and had a terrible mouth feel.
Yummy salad creations. You can build your own but I suggest trying one of theirs since it's a perfected concoction
Amazing healthy food. Reasonable prices for large quantity. Very fresh, super delicious.
Curry cauliflower salad is superb!

Love the fresh tasty foods, transparency with farmer/suppliers listed in each location, and emphasis on minimizing waste!! Awesome company. Make sure your employees ask if ppl are dining in, so they can use a washable bowl :-)
Healthy food quickly and at a reasonable price. Very clean and people are nice. Four stars because I'm not the biggest fan of the drink selection but still decent
Food is amazing. Poor abrupt customer service let’s this amazing business down :(
Great salad.... lengthy wait at lunch
Salads and bowls are great but you should be prepared for a wait unless you preorder online.

Had to run out to grab a quick bite while working at the Chicago Cultural Center. It's just down the street, so quick to get to. Good selection of vegetables to pick from, and some things I'd never thought about, like raw beets.  The service was very good, the workers were very attentive and made my salad quickly. It was well after the lunch rush, so it was a little slow. I usually find people less attentive and standing around talking, not quick to help you, but this was not the case.  I don't think anyone after me waited more than a few seconds to be helped.  The only reason I gave 4 not 5 stars is the salad was way over dressed. I asked for medium and it came as if I asked for extra heavy with a little more on top. Keep an eye out if that bothers you.

I ate here today twice! The staff was super friendly walking me through the menu. TWICE! Both times I absolutely loved the salad and plan to eat here during my whole trip. I tried every salad chain in Chicago and this is by far my favorite!
Just wish it was a tad cheaper. Other than that the staff is always super nice and the salads are amazing!!
I ordered the Shroomami and absolutely loved it - I almost ate it all! Service was very very rude and did not smile at us once, which turned us off to it at first, but the food makes up for it.
For vegetarians: Shroomami is decent, thai bowl is really bad. Their tofu sucks in general.
Good healthy food. I had the spring chicken.

Service is typically great at this location! Awesome salads and salad ingredient options. As a healthy picky eater, I have one request... PLEASE DO NOT GET RID OF THE "Mexican Corn Elote Bowl"!!! Make it a regular featured warm bowl menu item.

Honestly, not sure why there's a line out the door every day. It's good. But is it wait in line 20 minutes good? Not really. That said, if you ever see there's no wait, then sure. The salads are pretty tasty and I like the vibe and decor. But it's definitely not worth a crazy long wait.
Very good salads (if you don't mind spending a bit of cash 😊). The salads change per season so there's always something new to try.  BTW, I do believe they are cashless here so bring a card.
Love the options. Very tasty
The perfect place for a healthy weeknight dinner.

Great dressing. Just be on the lookout for disruptive and violet delinquents entering the store and demanding money and cursing at you. Was a one off incident in our case for sure. Good staff and fresh food though.
Super clean!! Great vegetarian choices and the freshest salad I ever had so yummy,
Bad Customer service. they do not deserve even the star.

Fantastic range of tasty salads.  For the Millennium Park location be prepared for 10-20 minute wait during lunch unless you order online ahead of time.  Same prices as other downtown eating locations so don't expect to save money compared to elsewhere.  Really great option for something a bit different than  fast-food and faster than sitting down somewhere.
Excellent and delicious salad 🥗 options. No sugar beverages are delicious as well!

Overall: The greatness of sweetgreen flavors are still there, but the service could be better.  The good: Like all sweetgreens, this one is a go-to for salad lovers or healthy "bowl" eaters. All the typical SG combinations are there and they're all just as delicious as they usually are.  The not-so-good: The poorer rating for this location is that on multiple occasions now, the service has been spotty at best. They are not friendly or helpful, almost to the point of uninviting. Also, like all sweetgreens, the prices are a few dollars too high for what you get.  Atmosphere:7/10 Service: 5/10 Food: 8.5/10
Great drinks.

This is a great lunch place and offers some great salads. The salads have a lot of different options, my favorite was the beets and goat cheese salad. You can create your own as well, which is always nice. Also they have a great online ordering system if you just need to pick up an go. They have some good tea options as well for drinks, which is a nice change from the regular options found at most quick service restaraunts. Be aware that this place does not take cash so make sure you have your card. If you're looking for a great salads, give this palace a try.
I love this place! The shroomami bowl is excellent. I always feel very welcomed by the staff.
Great location, fast service.
Lots of variety.
My new favorite lunch place!!! SO GOOD. SO YUMMY.
Yummy
My salad was top notch, super fresh

I had the shroomami bowl. It was good but way too heavy on the kale. Made me feel like I was chewing on leaves too much. The mushrooms and dressing were great though. The cashless thing is an inconvenience for travellers/tourists like me.
Very good place to eat healthy
Nice place to have healthy food. It's located near the park but not crowded.
This place is great! Came for their debut and had a free Shroomami.
